Chase Parker https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chase_Parker 0 Chase Parker (born April 22, 1994) is an American child actor who was born in San Bernardino County, California. He is the grandson of actress Eleanor Parker and nephew of Paul Day Clemens, Jr. Chase Parker started acting when he was only 2 years old, and his TV debut was for an Arby's commercial. Then, in 1998 he acted in his first TV show, General Hospital as a younger version of Nikolas Cassadine. In 1999, he played as Benjy Evans in Sunset Beach and guest starred in 7th Heaven as a younger version of Matt. He finished at The Woodlands High School.
